## Known Issues (from architecture reviews)

### Scene
- [ ] Remove dead code: `renderBuffer` / `lockedBuffer` declared but never used
- [ ] Add entity deletion / modification API (currently create-only)
- [ ] Document / validate `NurbsSurface::GetNormal()` midpoint assumption for highly curved surfaces

### Analysis
- [ ] Fix `Slice::At()` sequential pairing — incorrect for non-convex cross-sections
      or faces with more than 2 edge crossings per loop
- [ ] Consolidate Z-bounds scan shared by ThinSection, SmallFeature, Stringing
      into a single pre-pass to eliminate redundant O(V) vertex scans per solid
- [ ] Replace `Analysis` Meyer's singleton with dependency-injected instance

### Renderer
- [ ] **Viewport depth / layering (open)** — symptoms & probes: [2026-04-27] Viewport depth
      & occluded edges below
- [ ] Remove duplicated triangulation logic between `Patch::AddFace` and
      `AnalysisRenderer::TriangulateFace` (~60 lines duplicated)
- [ ] Investigate incremental / dirty-only GPU upload to replace full
      CPU rebuild + re-upload on every scene change
- [ ] Break `Display::InitUI()` out of Display — hardcoded UI layout couples
      display to UI structure

### Input
- [ ] Introduce `IDisplay` interface so Input can be tested without a real Display
- [ ] Design keyboard shortcut system (currently modifier keys checked inline)

### UI
- [ ] Split `UIRenderer::Render()` — decouple GL mesh building from ImGui draw calls
- [ ] Remove legacy string-based `SetSectionVisible` / `SetSectionValue` after
      direct `Panel*` access is fully adopted everywhere
- [ ] Move `Section::collapsed` expand/collapse control onto the element itself
      (currently driven externally by the renderer)

### SessionLogger
- [ ] Replace Meyer's singleton with injected instance for testability
- [ ] Make flush path configurable (currently hardcoded to `"session_log.json"`)
- [ ] Add automatic `SessionState` sync so callers cannot write stale state silently

