## [2026-04-27] Viewport depth & occluded edges (open)
Source: session investigation vs reference viewers; probes in `include/RenderingExperiments.hpp`,
`ViewportDepthExperiments`, `Display` / `OpenGLRenderer` depth and line passes.

### Observed symptoms (may not all appear every session)
- [ ] **Through-surface visibility** — internal or farther geometry (including triangulation
      stripes on curved faces) can show through nominally opaque front faces; severity varies
      with **camera / orbit** (grazing views often worse).
- [ ] **Same class on filled patches** — **lighting** (diffuse on `basic.frag`), **analysis tint**
      (vertex colors from `Patch` + `AnalysisResults`), and **hover / pick highlight fills** can
      all show **wrong depth layering**, not only wireframe lines. Implicates **triangle depth**
      (precision, coplanar/double geometry, MSAA) rather than the GS line pass alone.
- [ ] **Pick vs occlusion** — hover pick can hit entities that should be hidden behind nearer
      solid surfaces.
- [ ] **Fainter ghost edges** — edges that *should* be fully occluded by layering sometimes
      still appear but **weaker / thinner** than true silhouette or foreground edges (partial
      depth-test wins or line vs patch interaction). Repro is **intermittent**; depth prepass
      (`kDepthPrepassOpaquePatches`) has been reported to **slightly** change ghost edge intensity
      without fixing root cause.

### Investigation notes
- **`kDebugSkipSceneWireframe`** — if artifacts **persist** with wire pass off, focus on
      shaded tris / mesh / projection depth; if they **vanish**, line pass still matters.
- Tightening ortho clip (incl. view-scaled axis extent), pick polygon offset, wire Z bias,
      back-face cull for patches, and STL coplanar merge skips were tried without clearing the
      core artifact class.
- Default framebuffer MSAA: `RenderingExperiments::kGlFramebufferMsaaSamples` — **0 vs 4**
      reproduced **same** layering artifact (2026 session); MSAA unlikely primary cause here.
      Log still reports `GL_SAMPLES` / `GL_SAMPLE_BUFFERS` after context creation.
- **Reverse-Z** — `RenderingExperiments::kReverseZDepth` + `ProjectionDepthMode::EffectiveProjection`
      (rebuild). Clears depth to **0**, **`GL_GEQUAL`**, wire Z nudge sign flips. Session report:
      **no visible change** vs forward for same layering bug (ortho + likely **equal-Z** / mesh);
      startup log line in renderer confirms which mode is active. **Projection sync**: `Display::Frame`
      now always calls `SetCamera` after clip so near/far match the GPU every frame.
- **Degenerate patch tris** — `kCullDegeneratePatchTriangles` (**bool**) + `kDegeneratePatchMinCrossLen`
      (**double**, used only when cull is on) in `Patch::AddFace`. Session: toggling cull and
      thresholds **1e-13–1e-15** had **no** visible effect → artifact probably not from earcut
      zero-area triangles; look at **coplanar non-degenerate** duplicates / shell topology / capture.
- Use `/` bug marker + `session_log.json` (camera, clip, `depth_experiment_ordinal`) when a
      bad frame is visible to preserve repro state even if the artifact is hard to re-hit.

